    if Age is > 40 and Age is < 51 and Gender is female then NormedL will be 100 * normprob( ( RawL - LAveFemale41_50 ) / LSDFemale41_50 ) confidence 1.00;
    if Age is > 50 and Age is < 61 and Gender is female then NormedL will be 100 * normprob( ( RawL - LAveFemale51_60 ) / LSDFemale51_60 ) confidence 1.00;
    if Age is > 60 and Age is < 71 and Gender is female then NormedL will be 100 * normprob( ( RawL - LAveFemale61_70 ) / LSDFemale61_70 ) confidence 1.00;
    }    